variables that don’t matter or VIF issues

  • income
  • most of the sourcing channels, except D (D is sig)
  • residence area type
  • premium

income + premium should matter, maybe VIF?? or need some kind of combination term

varImp(lr1)

ROC , AUC simplest model

lr1pred <- predict(lr1, trainCC, type = 'resp')
head(lr1pred)
##         1         2         3         4         5         6 
## 0.9414003 0.9834927 0.1982772 0.9818793 0.9897420 0.9051843
trainCC$pred <- lr1pred
trainCC$predBinary <- as.integer(ifelse(trainCC$pred >= .90, 1, 0)) ## increased to up sensit
head(trainCC)
simplest <- ggplot(trainCC, aes(d=renewal, m = pred))+geom_roc()
